<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-04-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-04-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Griscom</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-06"><hi rend="italic">April 6,
                                        1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Griscom says, regarding the proposals of Italian minister for
                                foreign affairs (Signor Tittoni) concerning The Hague Conference, he
                                may add that Signor Tittoni told him informally that the Italian
                                delegates to the conference would neither take part in the
                                discussion nor vote on the question of limitation of armaments.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>